      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I applaud the many women who took part in the Million Mom March (front page, May 15) to demonstrate their support of gun-control regulations. I suggest a simpler solution: regulating ammunition.</p>
        <p>Why not require that all bullets have a microchip with identification, so that any bullet could be traced to the individual who bought it? Perhaps if people who bought ammunition were held liable for its use, they would be less cavalier about gun use.</p>
        <p>DOROTHY LEIDNER  Dallas, May 17, 2000</p>
      </block>
